revision.text: A bassist is somebody who plays a [[bass guitar]] or [[double bass]].

A bassist is somebody who plays a [[bass guitar]] or [[double bass]]. Famous bassists include: * [[Ron Carter]] * [[Les Claypool]] from [[Primus]] * [[John Entwistle]] from [[The Who]] * [[Kelly Grouchet]] from [[Electric Light Orchestra]] * [[Glenn Hughes]] from [[Deep Purple]] * [[Lemmy Kilmister]] from [[Motorhead]] * Sir [[Paul McCartney]] from [[The Beatles]] * [[Charles Mingus]] * [[Jason Newsted]] from [[Metallica]] * [[Sting]] from [[The Police]] * [[Leon Wilkeson]] from [[Lynyrd Skynyrd]]
